# ============================================================================
# Configuration Notes
# ============================================================================

# AGENT_SEED:
# - Must be unique and kept secret
# - If using mailbox, must MATCH the seed in Agentverse
# - Changing seed = different agent address

# MAILBOX_KEY:
# - If set (any value), mailbox mode is ENABLED
# - If not set or empty, agent runs in LOCAL mode
# - For production with Agentverse: set to "enabled" or any non-empty value
# - For local development: remove or leave empty

# MERCHANT_AGENT_ADDRESS:
# - Your Solana wallet address where payments will be sent
# - For testnet: Use Solana devnet address
# - For production: Use Solana mainnet address
# - Get testnet SOL from: https://faucet.solana.com/

# PAYMENT_NETWORK:
# - solana-devnet (testing)
# - solana-mainnet (production)
# - base-sepolia (testnet, requires x402)
# - base-mainnet (production, requires x402)

# ============================================================================
# Mailbox Setup (for Agentverse integration)
# ============================================================================

# Step 1: Add MAILBOX_KEY to this file (any non-empty value)
# Step 2: Deploy merchant-agentverse.py to Agentverse
# Step 3: In Agentverse, set AGENT_SEED to MATCH this file
# Step 4: Run: uv run merchant.py
# Step 5: Verify both agents show same address in logs

# With mailbox enabled:
# - Agent receives messages via Agentverse (24/7 availability)
# - Full x402 + Solana + EVM support (runs locally)
# - Best for production deployments

# Without mailbox (local only):
# - Agent only receives messages when running
# - All features still work
# - Best for development/testing

